# Ops, Security, and Release System ([PROJECT_NAME])

Read when: deploying, hardening, incident handling, or release/risk review.
Skip when: never.

Consolidated operations governance for deployment, secrets, security automation, observability, and release control.

## 1) Tiered Requirements
- Tier A: baseline only (advanced sections may be `N/A` with rationale)
- Tier B: baseline + recommended advanced controls
- Tier C: all controls required

## 2) Secrets Policy (Baseline)
- No secrets in source control.
- No secrets in docs/changelogs/issues.
- Separate values for local/dev/prod.
- Keep secret ownership defined.

## 3) Deployment + Rollback
### Preconditions
- [ ] Verify gate passes
- [ ] Required env vars present
- [ ] Backup/restore process validated (B/C)
- [ ] Local runtime profile validated (if using compose/tunnel)

### Deploy Steps
1. Pull release candidate.
2. Apply environment values.
3. Start/update services.
4. Run smoke checks.

### Local Runtime Notes
- Compose/local run command: `[LOCAL_ONLY_RUN_COMMAND]`
- Optional tunnel profile: `[TUNNEL_PROFILE_COMMAND_OR_NA]`

### Rollback
1. Stop failed release.
2. Restore prior known-good version.
3. Restore backup if needed.
4. Re-run smoke checks.

